# Global preferences

Durable behaviors that apply across all projects. Project-specific
conventions belong in the project's own `CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md`.

## Maintaining this file

- The shared sections below are chezmoi-generated; edit the source, not this
  rendered file. See the `agent-contracts` skill for the workflow.
- When you learn a durable, cross-project behavior preference, update the
  matching source: shared behaviors go in the partials, Claude-only preferences
  go in this file's own sections below. Per-project memory is for facts that
  only matter inside one repo.
- Write entries as imperative instructions to yourself, not as descriptions
  of the user's habits.
- Do not include specific incident examples to illustrate a rule. State the
  rule itself; the example belongs in the conversation that produced it.
- Before adding a rule, check whether it fits an existing section. Keep this
  file compact.

